channel.title: This compile error seriously doesn't make sense
channel.description:
Hey everyone,
Alright, now let's get straight to the point. I use Dementhium 637/639.
So this is the compile error I get;
[code]src\org\dementhium\content\activity\impl\ZombiesActivity.java:100: error: cannot find symbol int slot = player.getCaveIndex(); ^ symbol: method getCaveIndex() location: variable player of type Player src\org\dementhium\content\activity\impl\ZombiesActivity.java:102: error: cannot find symbol player.setCaveIndex(0); ^ symbol: method setCaveIndex(int) location: variable player of type Player src\org\dementhium\content\activity\impl\ZombiesActivity.java:134: error: cannot find symbol int earned = ((int)Math.ceil((player.getSettings().getKilledZomb ies() > 0 ? wave*2 : 0)) ^ symbol: method getKilledZombies() location: class Settings src\org\dementhium\content\activity\impl\ZombiesActivity.java:135: error: cannot find symbol +player.getSettings().getKilledZombies()); ^ symbol: method getKilledZombies() location: class Settings src\org\dementhium\content\activity\impl\ZombiesActivity.java:146: error: cannot find symbol player.getSettings().setKilledZombies(0); ^ symbol: method setKilledZombies(int) location: class Settings src\org\dementhium\content\activity\impl\ZombiesActivity.java:269: error: method does not override or implement a method from a supertype @Override ^ 6 errors Press any key to continue . . .[/code]
Like seriously, what dafuq is "variable player of type Player" ... seriously doesn't fucking make sense.
Please reply ASAP.
Cheers, I Pk 22.
